(180, 2, '2014-08-03 22:44:42', '2014-08-03 22:44:42', '&nbsp;\n\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">Consultations</h2>\n\n<a href="http://www.mostlyconcretellc.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/Hard_Digging.png"><img class="alignright wp-image-96 size-medium fill-screen-on-mobile" src="http://www.mostlyconcretellc.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/Hard_Digging-261x300.png" alt="Hard_Digging" width="261" height="300" /></a> Maybe like other concrete contractors it is time to re-build, analyze what works and what isn''t working. It may be time to get honest and get rid of services and inventory that don''t work or are too costly to deliver in today’s marketplace.\n\n"How" is good question. So maybe there isn''t a problem. "This is the way we have always done it" is my favorite response. It says that we are so invested in a program that doesn''t really work great. It has problems but its <span style="text-decoration: underline;">our way</span> to conduct and track work even if it doesn''t work. We can help growing your staff and craftsman in house, building teams that are cost effective, efficient and meet the requirements that your clients demand. We can show you how changing the culture can contribute to a better bottom line and improve communication of vision and goals of primary stakeholders.   Or you could\n\n<blockquote>Keep doing what you have been doing and expect different results. If nothing changes, nothing changes</blockquote>', 'Consultations', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '16-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-08-03 22:44:42', '2014-08-03 22:44:42', '', 16, 'http://www.mostlyconcretellc.com/16-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
