(206, 2, '2014-08-13 07:34:29', '2014-08-13 07:34:29', 'Thoughts of times spent\nWhile the concrete truck backs through the fog\nCatching the morning’s red glare \nAnd passing thru the neighbor’s fence. \nThink of me when the mist rises from the mud \nAnd the bleed water pools in the low places too far away. \nThink of me then when the stake pierces the water and gas line\n Watch the flames shoot out from the water’s stream\nThink of me when a form setter smacks his shin with a sledge.\n And calls out in the low moan to God and Mother. \nThink of me when a labor trips over some rebar \nWhile rushing to pull steel \n Like it was the most important thing he''ll do \nRecall these times when the machine would ride \nThe waves of concrete and dance wildly, \nWonderfully through the hold downs and pipes\n To deposit you off to the one side in a pile\n Then dance away with out rider all the while. \nThink of me then. Brothers of the wet and knurly\nWhen the float sticks to hard cream\nAnd your fingers bleed from those little raspberries\nSatan’s fruit of the fruitless labor\nBurning in the desert’s sun, blinded by a labor’s wage.\nOne more day closer to giving it the landlord’s hand\nAnd feeding those little mouths that suffer a mean old man \nListening to the sing of trowels working like a team\nOr the stumble of shovels and madman on the chute\nCursing and spitting out commands as he struggles \nWith machines and man', 'Concrete dog', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '205-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-08-13 07:34:29', '2014-08-13 07:34:29', '\r\n\r\n\r\nThoughts of times spent\r\nWhile the concrete truck backs through the fog\r\nCatching the morning’s red glare \r\nAnd passing thru the neighbor’s fence. \r\nThink of me when the mist rises from the mud \r\nAnd the bleed water pools in the low places too far away. \r\nThink of me then when the stake pierces the water and gas line\r\n Watch the flames shoot out from the water’s stream\r\nThink of me when a form setter smack